As President and Chief Operating Officer of Halbert Hargrove, JC is charged with the day-to-day running of the firm. Execution and operational excellence are his bywords; we consider him our glue. JC has had the privilege to be involved in most facets of the firm, and has enjoyed being part of HH’s growth and success. He says he enjoys the dynamic nature of his role: “I like solving big challenges.” 
He joined HH as Operations Manager in 1996.
JC earned his Bachelor of Science in Business Administration with a Finance emphasis from the Colegio de Estudios Superiores de Administracion in Bogota, Colombia, and his MBA from University of Redlands School of Business. He was awarded the ACCREDITED INVESTMENT FIDUCIARY™ designation by the University of Pittsburgh-affiliated Center for Fiduciary Studies. In 2016, JC earned a LEAD Certificate in Corporate Innovation from Stanford Graduate School of Business. He was part of Stanford’s Pioneer cohort—the first group of leaders to engage in this leadership program.
Married to Ruth for 25 years, JC is dad to Nico and Isabella. He serves on the Board of JSerra Catholic High School—and is proud to have been honored as Father of the Year 2015 at Isabella’s school. The Abusaid family has two Boston Terriers, Max and Lola. JC’s commitment to exercising and eating healthy is legendary; call him a health freak, and he’ll take it as a compliment. Outside of the office, you’ll find him running, mountain biking, wakeboarding, and snowboarding.






James T. AhnCFP®, AIF®Wealth Advisor





 

James T. AhnCFP®, AIF®Wealth Advisorjahn@hhga.com



As a Wealth Advisor with Halbert Hargrove’s Long Beach office, James engages with and advises clients on decisions that strongly impact their financial lives. As he puts it, “Every outcome is driven by doing what is truly in clients’ best interests. This allows us to sit on the same side of the table when important financial choices are made.” James enjoys educating clients—including translating complex investment and insurance concepts into everyday language.
Prior to joining Halbert Hargrove in 2012, James worked as a financial advisor with Citi Personal Wealth Management as well as Edward Jones Investments. He says two of the aspects of working at HH he most appreciates are “the ability to be fully engaged in our clients’ lives—and to be under zero pressure to sell products or report quarterly earnings to shareholders.”
James earned a Bachelor of Arts degree in Political Science with an Emphasis on International Relations from the University of California, Los Angeles. He was awarded the ACCREDITED INVESTMENT FIDUCIARY™ designation by the University of Pittsburgh-affiliated Center for Fiduciary Studies and is a CERTIFIED FINANCIAL PLANNER™.
James is married to Sonia, an elementary school teacher with LAUSD—and is “dad” to two rescue dogs. Two things he’s particularly proud of: paying for his UCLA education by selling books door to door, and scoring four touchdowns in a single game. When on vacation, James likes to pretend that cell phones and Wi-Fi don’t exist.






Timothy J. AndersonCPA/PFS, CGMA, AIF®Managing Director





 

Timothy J. AndersonCPA/PFS, CGMA, AIF®Managing Directortanderson@hhga.com



Tim fosters great relationships with his clients; his objective is to assist them in all facets of their financial lives. Working with the Halbert Hargrove team, he builds and implements a disciplined, ongoing process that ensures that all the complexities inherent to his clients’ wealth are addressed. Tim has been with HH, based in our Long Beach office, since 1994. His longevity with the firm, he says, “gives me the opportunity to be a leader and play a part in developing the next generation. That’s very rewarding to me.”
Before joining HH, Tim was based in London, England, as a Founder, Principal and Director of Falcon Real Estate Investment Company, Ltd., serving institutional and individual property investors in Europe, the Middle East and Africa. Between 1989 and 1991, he was Vice President of Chase Manhattan Bank Private Banking, overseeing private client investments in the bank’s Europe, Middle East and Africa divisions.
Tim began his career with Russell Investments, advising institutional clients on their investment portfolios. He spent three of his 11 years with Russell on a Canadian assignment in the firm’s Toronto office.
Tim is a 1977 Business Administration graduate of Pacific Lutheran University and has served on the Executive Advisory Board of PLU’s School of Business. A CPA/PFS and CGMA, he has served in several leadership roles since 1994 at both the chapter and state levels with the California Society of Certified Public Accountants. He is also an active member of the American Institute of Certified Public Accountants. Tim was awarded the ACCREDITED INVESTMENT FIDUCIARY™ designation by the University of Pittsburgh-affiliated Center for Fiduciary Studies.
With his wife Kerry, he shares a home life with two children, a dog and four cats. Tim is proud of his service on the Long Beach Area Council of The Boy Scouts of America Shooting Sports Committee, as well as an Assistant Scoutmaster for his troop and a Council merit badge counselor for fishing, rifle and shotgun. An active sculler and member of the Long Beach Rowing Association, he is a Director of the Southern California Rowing Foundation, and a gold medalist in international rowing competition. In his down time, Tim likes to read and drive long distances to places he’s never been.






Yuyen Brian ChangCFP®, CFA, AIF®Wealth Advisor





 

Yuyen Brian ChangCFP®, CFA, AIF®Wealth Advisorbchang@hhga.com



Brian joined us as a Wealth Advisor with our Long Beach office in 2015. He contributes a rigorous background in investment analytics—including assessing risk exposures, conducting fundamental research, and advising on performance stability—to his relationships with HH clients. The bottom line for Brian is “getting to know clients and helping them make better financial decisions. I love knowing that HH is always on their side.”
Brian’s investment advisory career began in 2007 while he was still a college student, with internships at Merrill Lynch and A.G. Edwards and Sons. His most recent role prior to HH was as Portfolio Manager with GPS Capital Management. While there, Brian provided analytical support to the Chief Investment Officer for equity, fixed income, and option portfolios, and co-managed portfolios for more than 200 individuals and families across a range of investment strategies.
Before that time, Brian was a Wealth Planning Associate with investment advisor Wealth Design; Brian’s responsibilities included financial planning, investment analysis, and portfolio implementation for clients. He began his post-college career as a credit analyst with Provident Funding Associates.
Brian earned a B.S. degree in Business Administration from the University of California at Berkeley. He was awarded the ACCREDITED INVESTMENT FIDUCIARY™ designation by the University of Pittsburgh-affiliated Center for Fiduciary Studies and he is a CERTIFIED FINANCIAL PLANNER™. Brian is also a Certified Financial Analyst™ (CFA) Charterholder. Brian earned this certification, noted for its rigorous curriculum, after passing three sequential six-hour exams and completing four years of qualifying professional investment experience.
He is a native Chinese Mandarin speaker, and is fluent in reading and writing Mandarin as well. In his time away from the office, he enjoys movies, basketball, and spending time with family and friends.






Sathya CheyCFP®, AIF® Wealth AdvisorMBA USC





 

Sathya CheyCFP®, AIF® Wealth AdvisorMBA USCschey@hhga.com



As a Wealth Advisor with Halbert Hargrove in Long Beach, Sathya listens to her clients. Understanding their needs, concerns, and goals enables her to help them navigate important financial decisions, and craft and implement an investment process that is suited to their needs. Sathya places a strong focus on effective communications—helping clients understand the many complex financial decisions they may face as well as the complexities of their portfolios and investment markets.
“What drives my passion for what I do,” Sathya says, “is helping clients enjoy life. It is the greatest feeling to hear them tell me how they worry less knowing they have trusted advisors taking care of their investments—or seeing them being able to live the retirement lifestyle they hoped for funded from their investments.” Before joining HH in 2007, she was an assistant general manager and finance manager for Long Beach Auto Imports.
Sathya earned her Bachelor of Arts degree in Business Administration – Finance from California State University at Fullerton in 2007 and an MBA in 2015 from the University Of Southern California Marshall School of Business. She was awarded the ACCREDITED INVESTMENT FIDUCIARY™ designation by the University of Pittsburgh-affiliated Center for Fiduciary Studies and is a CERTIFIED FINANCIAL PLANNER™.
Sathya is derived from the Sanskrit word for truth. Sathya was born in a refugee camp in Thailand where her family fled after surviving the Cambodian genocide. She and her daughter Milana volunteer at their church and are parents to two cats: Tina Turner and Cleopatra. Sathya enjoys working out, as well as camping, hiking, and being active outdoors—and says the combination of live music and delicious food is her definition of heaven. 






Tony CollinsAIF®Client Service Manager





 

Tony CollinsAIF®Client Service Managertcollins@hhga.com



Tony joined our Long Beach team in 2016. He describes his role as “seeing things through.” His task, he says, is to ensure that clients’ needs and concerns are taken care of in a timely manner—and completed with careful, thoughtful detail. We value his initiative in seeking out ways to improve how clients experience working with HH. Tony welcomes “the high level of collaboration and support between team members. Each person brings something unique and interesting to the table. HH fosters a positive environment where I am pushed to constantly improve myself.”
He began his career in financial services in 2014 with UBS Financial Services, Inc. in Sarasota, Florida as an intern. The following year, Tony was hired as a Client Service Associate with UBS. As part of a six-member team, his chief role was to provide operational and administrative support to the team’s advisors.
Tony graduated from Eckerd College in St. Petersburg with a Bachelor’s degree in Business Administration. He also completed double minors in Finance and Economics. He was awarded the ACCREDITED INVESTMENT FIDUCIARY™ designation by the University of Pittsburgh-affiliated Center for Fiduciary Studies in 2016.
A sailor for his entire life, Tony was a member of Eckerd College’s nationally ranked collegiate sailing team. He continues to seek out new opportunities to sail, both for fun and competitively.
An unusual Collins family member is Tony’s 15-year old lizard—a female bearded dragon named Dragon. Thus far, Tony says, he has not succeeded in teaching her how to fly and breathe fire. Tony’s grandfather, on the other hand, “flies” in vintage Formula 1 car races. Tony travels around the world to watch him compete on major circuits: “I am his biggest fan and try to attend every race I can.”






Craig T. CrossAIF®Managing Director





 

Craig T. CrossAIF®Managing Directorccross@hhga.com



Craig is a Managing Director and Co-founder of Halbert Hargrove in Long Beach. He has been advising HH clients for more than three decades. Craig loves this work; he says he especially enjoys “the interactions I’m able to have with a broadly diversified group of truly nice and interesting clients and centers of influence.”
His background includes work with a United States Senator in Washington, D.C. and as a prime aide to the 1974 California Gubernatorial Nominee, Houston Flournoy. From 1975 to 1979, he was responsible for raising athletic scholarship support funds at California State University, Long Beach.
Craig earned a Bachelor’s Degree in Political Science from Stanford University in 1973. He is a Chartered Mutual Fund Counselor and has earned the ACCREDITED INVESTMENT FIDUCIARY™ designation from the University of Pittsburgh-affiliated Center for Fiduciary Studies. 
Some things about Craig has that most people don’t know: He ran with the bulls in Pamplona, Spain. He has thrown out a first pitch at Angels Stadium. And he’s proud to say he’s attended both a Navy SEALS and a TOPGUN graduation. The accomplishments he is most proud of: His three children, who have completed their undergraduate studies at Chapman University, Stanford University, and the University of Arizona.






Shane W. CummingsCFP®, AIF®Director Of Operations MBA Chapman





 

Shane W. CummingsCFP®, AIF®Director Of Operations MBA Chapmanscummings@hhga.com



Shane is based on Halbert Hargrove’s Denver office and holds multiple roles with Halbert Hargrove.  As Director of Operations, Shane’s overriding objective is to enable Halbert Hargrove associates to work efficiently and effectively, while safeguarding client data.  As Wealth Advisor, he works with clients in helping them determine goals and identify financial risks, creating an allocation strategy for their investments
Shane oversees the technology infrastructure of the firm, managing HH’s financial data systems to keep them running smoothly and securely. He interfaces with custodians and technology providers to acquire and implement best-of-breed technology and processes. Shane joined Halbert Hargrove in 2006, and was promoted to HH’s management team in 2012.
Shane says he relishes being challenged with new projects and issues from day to day: “The job is never static. It gives me lots of opportunities to hone new skills and find new solutions for our clients.”
Previously, Shane was a mortgage associate at Argent Mortgage Company. His responsibilities there included setting up new loan accounts, processing property appraisals, researching tax and title information, and providing support to account managers.
Shane received his Bachelor of Arts degree in Communication from UC San Diego in 2003 and his MBA from Chapman University in 2007. He earned the ACCREDITED INVESTMENT FIDUCIARY™ designation from the University of Pittsburgh-affiliated Center for Fiduciary Studies and he is a CERTIFIED FINANCIAL PLANNER™.
He met his wife Gillian while studying in Scotland. At the top of his list of favorite pursuits is spending time with Gillian and their young daughter, exposing her to new places and experiences. They enjoy traveling to Europe to spend time with family, visit interesting cities, and explore historically and culturally rich places.






Robert A. DouglisAIF®Regional Director





 

Robert A. DouglisAIF®Regional Directorrdouglis@hhga.com



Rob is based in our Long Beach headquarters. He joined Halbert Hargrove as a Regional Director in 2016. Rob has successfully advised clients in managing their investment assets for more than two decades. One of the best things about his current role, he says, is his ability to “build long-lasting client relationships with a great firm behind me.”
For Rob, ongoing communications with clients are critical. This includes “helping my clients fully understand our investment approach with regard to their goals and investment objectives.” HH’s asset allocation strategies, he points out, aim to help clients achieve consistent returns while mitigating risk on the downside. “My experience in helping guide clients through two bear markets plays a valuable role in communicating and helping set the right expectations.”
Before joining HH, Rob was an investment consultant with TD Ameritrade for six years, where he evaluated portfolios and helped clients manage their assets from a big-picture, goals perspective. Prior to that, he held similar roles with Wells Fargo Advisors and WM Financial Services. He earned a Bachelor of Arts in Economics from California State University, Northridge, and was awarded the ACCREDITED INVESTMENT FIDUCIARY™ designation by the University of Pittsburgh-affiliated Center for Fiduciary Studies.
Rob’s commitments outside of work include his passion for ice hockey. He works as an Off-Ice Official for the NHL, performing stats at Anaheim Ducks Games. He also enjoys heading with his family to Disneyland, where they hold annual passes. What Rob is most proud of is his role as a father and husband. He and his wife Kimberly share four children, Kristen, Hannah, Tony, and Jacob— and two cats, Oliver and Lilly.






