Tyler GilleyAIF®Client Service Manager





 

Tyler GilleyAIF®Client Service Managertgilley@hhga.com



Tyler was promoted to Client Service Manager with our Long Beach team in 2017. In big-picture terms, he sees his role as helping people. This covers the gamut of responding to clients’ needs, concerns, and services, and making sure his team is working efficiently “so that our clients can get the help they need to reach their goals.”
What Tyler finds especially rewarding in his work are his interactions with people—particularly, he says, when it’s clear that he’s making a difference in supporting positive outcomes. He also values the opportunity to work alongside “incredibly talented and knowledgeable individuals who are helping me grow in my knowledge and understanding of personal finance and investments.”
Tyler joined HH as an operations intern in 2014. After he graduated from California State University Long Beach late that year, we invited him to join us in a full-time role as Operations and Training Specialist in January 2015. His responsibilities included assisting with IT support, generating client reports, and maintaining HH’s internal client database. As Tyler explains it, he focused on “creating systems and structures to help make the whole company run more efficiently—and mitigate chaos.”
Tyler earned a Bachelor of Science in Business Finance from CSU Long Beach; he also minored in Spanish. While there, he co-managed three separate portfolios in excess of $250,000 in a CSU student-led program, the Student Managed Investment Fund (SMIF), for one year.
Outside of work, Tyler volunteers with his church’s high school ministry. He leads group discussions among students, and helps run sound and lighting systems and produce events, including summer and winter camps. He also enjoys getting out of the city and going camping or shooting with friends.






Gary N. HickokRegional Director





 

Gary N. HickokRegional Directorghickok@hhga.com



A Regional Director with Halbert Hargrove’s San Diego office since 1992, Gary focuses on developing wealth maximization programs for individuals and families.
Over the years, he’s served as a trusted advisor to families across generations. A big highlight of his work, he says, is the relationships he’s built with clients and his HH associates. 
Gary has also been instrumental in designing and implementing participant training programs and retirement planning seminars, as well as addressing 404-C compliance issues, for both Fortune 500 and local companies throughout Southern California.
Gary’s background prior to 1992 includes serving as: Regional Vice President of MetroBank, San Diego; Regional Vice President of United Bank of Arizona, Phoenix; Vice President of Union Bank, Los Angeles; and Captain/Reconnaissance Officer, United States Marine Corps.
He graduated from Youngstown State University in 1971, and has been awarded the ACCREDITED INVESTMENT FIDUCIARY™ designation by the University of Pittsburgh-affiliated Center for Fiduciary Studies.
Dad to daughter Haley and son Matt, Gary enjoys spending time with family and friends when away from work. A model railroad enthusiast for decades, he realized his dream of sharing that passion in 2014. Gary created the Old Town Model Railroad Depot, the largest O Scale exhibit open to the public in the Western U.S.






Russell T. HillCFP®, AIFA®Chairman/CEO of Halbert Hargrove Global Advisors LLC MBA Stanford





 

Russell T. HillCFP®, AIFA®Chairman/CEO of Halbert Hargrove Global Advisors LLC MBA Stanfordrhill@hhga.com



Russ has led Long Beach-headquartered Halbert Hargrove Global Advisors for more than four decades. Currently, he is Chairman & CEO—and has happily handed off most of the firm’s day-to-day responsibilities to the next generation.
Russ has contributed his time, expertise and energies to community initiatives for many years. He served as Chair of the Long Beach Memorial Medical Center, Community Hospital of Long Beach, and Miller Children’s Hospital Governing Boards and is now serving a second time in these roles. In addition, he is Chair of the Investment Committee for MemorialCare Health Services.
A related passion is fostering solutions to aging-related challenges. Russ serves on the Advisory Council for Stanford University’s Center on Longevity. He initiated the Center’s Design Challenge Series in 2014 and provided the impetus for their multi-year longevity and well-being project, Sightlines.
Other past engagements include serving as President of Stanford Business School Alumni Association, President of Family Services of Long Beach, President of Long Beach Rotary, and six-time Chairman of SCAN Healthplan. Russ is also a co-founder of William Hill Winery and was Founding Vice-Chairman/Treasurer and three-term Chairman of the Long Beach Aquarium of the Pacific, where he still serves on the Board. He also served as Chair of the Desegregation Funds Committee for the Long Beach Unified School District.
He received his BA in Economics from Stanford University and his MBA from the Stanford Graduate School of Business.
Russ and his wife, Avalon reside (mostly) in Long Beach and partly (not enough) in Cortona, Italy.






Elliott C. HollingsworthAIF®Regional Director MBA USC





 

Elliott C. HollingsworthAIF®Regional Director MBA USCehollingsworth@hhga.com



As a Regional Director with Halbert Hargrove’s Long Beach office, Elliott helps guide clients in making the critical decisions that impact their financial lives, including establishing goals and objectives, and determining suitable risk and asset allocations. He also works with them to uncover potentially problematic areas. Among his strengths is helping clients understand the value of HH’s investment approach and wealth advisory services: “This, coupled with our discovery process, reinforces for clients how HH as a firm fully understands their current situation. In turn, they feel confident and supported in meeting their financial goals.”  
Elliott has more than 15 years’ experience in providing fiduciary investment management and wealth advisory services to successful individuals, families, and corporate clients. What he enjoys most about his current role, he says, is “getting to know new and prospective clients, and learning about their career paths and future aspirations.”
Before joining HH in 2014, Elliott was a vice president with Oakwood Capital Management in Los Angeles for seven years. As a senior member of Oakwood’s private client wealth management group, he provided ongoing integrated wealth management solutions—investment, tax, and estate planning guidance—to his clients. Prior to Oakwood, he worked for Merrill Lynch as a financial advisor for six years.
Elliott earned his MBA from the University of Southern California Marshall School of Business in 2008 and his B.S. from Vanderbilt University in 1998. He was awarded the ACCREDITED INVESTMENT FIDUCIARY™ designation by the University of Pittsburgh-affiliated Center for Fiduciary Studies.
Elliott and his wife Lindsay are raising children George and Eloise; his favorite pursuit is spending time with them, followed by playing basketball, golf, and running. As a family the Hollingsworths are actively involved with Kidspace Children’s Museum in Pasadena as well as Children’s Hospital of Los Angeles.






Mark P. JanciCFP®, CPWA®, AIF®Regional Director





 

Mark P. JanciCFP®, CPWA®, AIF®Regional Directormjanci@hhga.com



Mark manages our Bellevue, Washington office; he joined Halbert Hargrove in 2005 to establish the firm’s presence in the Pacific Northwest. He has been advising clients for more than 25 years. For Mark, the relationships he establishes with his clients mean a lot: “I invest my time to understand each unique situation they present, and to be intuitive—applying my experience of working with sophisticated clients to plan and choose wisely to manage and protect their wealth.”
Mark serves as an investment adviser to affluent individuals and institutions, working with a diverse client base that includes entrepreneurs, professionals, technology company executives, and retirees. As a member of both the Seattle and East King County Estate Planning Councils, he assists and guides clients in legacy planning. Mark is an active member of HH’s Wealth Advisory Committee.
Before 2005, Mark was an Investment Management and Trust Consultant for Northwestern Mutual Wealth Management Group. Concurrently, he served as a fee-based Financial Planning Specialist with Network Planning Advisors, LLC.
Mark earned his B.A. in Sociology cum laude from Washington State University and his M.A. in College Student Personnel from Bowling Green State University. He was awarded his ACCREDITED INVESTMENT FIDUCIARY™ designation by the University of Pittsburgh-affiliated Center for Fiduciary Studies, and his Certified Private Wealth Advisor (CPWA®) certification from the Investment Management Consultants Association. He is an active member of the National Financial Planning Association (FPA) and is also a CERTIFIED FINANCIAL PLANNER®.
Mark contributes his time and energies outside of work to support several non-profits. He’s active with East Side Academy, a private high school for at-risk youth, and supports several college scholarship programs. He enjoys fine woodworking, cycling, and golf—and his favorite instrument is his Martin D41 guitar. Mark likes his vacations to be unstructured, unscripted, and spontaneous. He enjoys traveling overseas with his wife Mary: taking in the adventurous cultural experiences and food tasting.
 






Beverly KarnsAIF®Regional DirectorMBA New York University Stern School of Business 





 

Beverly KarnsAIF®Regional DirectorMBA New York University Stern School of Business bkarns@hhga.com



Beverly joined Halbert Hargrove’s Denver office as a Regional Director in 2017. She has worked in wide-ranging roles in the investment management industry for 25 years, building great relationships with her clients and the community. Hard-working and focused, Beverly ensures her team successfully guide clients towards reaching their financial goals, all in a professional and kind environment.
Before joining HH, Beverly served as Managing Director of Debt/Equity Financing with Capitol Peak Asset Management, leading the firm in providing senior debt financing and project finance for infrastructure opportunities in rural America.  Prior to that time, Beverly spent five years as a Vice President in the Wealth Strategies group at Northern Trust and Alliance Bernstein. Her responsibilities included new business development and strategic financial planning for clients ranging from businesses and nonprofits to family offices and high net-worth individuals.
Beverly spent the majority of her career in New York City and Denver working in the institutional equity divisions of Donaldson, Lufkin & Jenrette (DLJ), Credit Suisse First Boston, SG Warburg and NorthSouth Capital. In these positions, she provided equity research, IPOs, and trading to many of the largest fund companies in the nation.
Beverly earned a B.S. in Business Administration from Iowa State University and an M.B.A. in finance from New York University’s Stern School of Business. She holds memberships with Financial Executive International (FEI), Colorado Philanthropic Advisors Network (CPAN), Denver Estate Planning Council, Rocky Mountain Estate Planning Counsel, and the Association for Corporate Growth (ACG).
Away from work, Beverly’s active community involvement includes volunteering with her children’s school, Kent Denver. She serves as Treasurer for the Endowment Board of The Gathering Place, a shelter for homeless women and children, and also serves on the Advisory Board of the Denver Scholarship Foundation.
Beverly and her husband John are raising three children, Catherine, Madison, and Johnny. Her favorite way to unwind is family time—cooking at home or watching her children’s sports and music concerts. A seasoned marathon runner, she also enjoys reading, tennis, skiing, and yoga.
 






