Patrick A. KujawaAIF®Regional Director





 

Patrick A. KujawaAIF®Regional Directorpkujawa@hhga.com



As a Regional Director with Halbert Hargrove’s Scottsdale office, Pat ensures that his team successfully guides clients towards reaching their financial objectives. “I take great satisfaction in helping others achieve their dreams and closely following the global markets,” he says. “I feel truly blessed in working with highly professional, ethical and kind teammates to improve our clients’ financial futures—brainstorming with them to develop creative solutions to clients’ challenges. I love what I do and look forward to going to the office each day.”
Pat has more than two decades of experience in private and institutional investing. Before joining HH in 2012, he was a Regional Director for AQR Capital Management in Scottsdale, marketing the firm’s alternative investment mutual funds to large advisory teams at brokerage firms in the Western U.S. Prior to AQR, he served high net worth clients as a principal with a niche financial advisory firm in Phoenix. Pat has worked at O’Shaughnessy Asset Management, JPMorgan Asset Management, and Strong Capital Management, and was a founding principal at Undiscovered Managers, LLC.
